
 DATE
üîπ What is DATE?
Stores only the date (no time).
Format:
YYYY-MM-DD
üîπ When to Use (Use Case)
	‚Ä¢ Date of birth
	‚Ä¢ Exam date
	‚Ä¢ Joining date
	‚Ä¢ Holiday date
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE students (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    dob DATE
);
Sample Data:
	‚Ä¢ Rahul ‚Üí 2006-05-12
	‚Ä¢ Anjali ‚Üí 2005-11-20

 TIME
üîπ What is TIME?
Stores only time (hours, minutes, seconds).
Format:
HH:MM:SS
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Login time
	‚Ä¢ School bell time
	‚Ä¢ Class start time
	‚Ä¢ Office shift time
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE login_log (
    username VARCHAR(50),
    login_time TIME
);
Sample Data:
	‚Ä¢ Suresh ‚Üí 09:30:00
	‚Ä¢ Kavya ‚Üí 14:45:10

DATETIME
üîπ What is DATETIME?
Stores both date and time together.
Format:
YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Login timestamp
	‚Ä¢ Order date & time
	‚Ä¢ Event date & time
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE user_login (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    login_datetime DATETIME
);
Sample Data:
	‚Ä¢ Ramesh ‚Üí 2025-01-10 09:15:00

 TIMESTAMP
üîπ What is TIMESTAMP?
Stores date and time, but:
	‚Ä¢ Automatically updates
	‚Ä¢ Depends on system time zone
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Record creation time
	‚Ä¢ Last update time
	‚Ä¢ Audit logs
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT,
    order_time TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
Sample Data:
	‚Ä¢ Order placed by Priya ‚Üí auto stored time

 YEAR
üîπ What is YEAR?
Stores only year.
Format:
YYYY
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Year of passing
	‚Ä¢ Year of joining
	‚Ä¢ Manufacturing year
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE students (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    pass_year YEAR
);
Sample Data:
	‚Ä¢ Manoj ‚Üí 2023
	‚Ä¢ Neha ‚Üí 2024

NOW() Function (Current Date & Time)
üîπ What is NOW()?
Returns current date and time.
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Store current login time
	‚Ä¢ Record transaction time
üîπ Example
INSERT INTO user_login VALUES ('Amit', NOW());

 CURDATE() Function (Current Date)
üîπ What is CURDATE()?
Returns current date only.
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Attendance date
	‚Ä¢ Today‚Äôs date entry
üîπ Example
INSERT INTO attendance VALUES ('Rohit', CURDATE());

CURTIME() Function (Current Time)
üîπ What is CURTIME()?
Returns current time only.
üîπ When to Use
	‚Ä¢ Login time
	‚Ä¢ Shift start time
üîπ Example
INSERT INTO login_log VALUES ('Sneha', CURTIME());

 DEFAULT with Date & Time
üîπ What is DEFAULT?
Automatically inserts date/time if not given.
üîπ Example
CREATE TABLE feedback (
    name VARCHAR(50),
    feedback_date DATE DEFAULT CURDATE()
);

 Comparison Table (Easy Memory)
Data Type	Stores	Use Case Example
DATE	Date only	DOB, exam date
TIME	Time only	Login time
DATETIME	Date + Time	Event timestamp
TIMESTAMP	Auto date + time	Logs, audits
YEAR	Year only	Pass year

 Simple Exam Line (Very Important)
	‚ÄúMySQL date and time data types are used to store dates, times, and timestamps for real-world applications like attendance, exams, and transactions.‚Äù

Conclusion (Simple)
	‚Ä¢ Use DATE for dates
	‚Ä¢ Use TIME for time
	‚Ä¢ Use DATETIME for date + time
	‚Ä¢ Use TIMESTAMP for auto logs
	‚Ä¢ Use YEAR for year values
Understanding these data types helps in building accurate and real-time databases.




CREATE DATABASE date_types_db;
USE date_types_db;

/* ‚É£ DATE DATA TYPE */
CREATE TABLE student_dob (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    dob DATE
);

INSERT INTO student_dob VALUES
(1,'Rahul','2006-05-12'),
(2,'Anjali','2005-11-20');


/*  TIME DATA TYPE */
CREATE TABLE login_time (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    login_time TIME
);

INSERT INTO login_time VALUES
(1,'Suresh','09:30:00'),
(2,'Kavya','14:45:10');


/*  DATETIME DATA TYPE */
CREATE TABLE user_login_datetime (
    login_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    login_datetime DATETIME
);

INSERT INTO user_login_datetime VALUES
(1,'Ramesh','2025-01-10 09:15:00'),
(2,'Priya','2025-01-10 18:40:00');


/* TIMESTAMP DATA TYPE */
CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_name VARCHAR(50),
    order_time TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

INSERT INTO orders (order_id, customer_name) VALUES
(1,'Amit'),
(2,'Neha');


/* YEAR DATA TYPE */
CREATE TABLE passing_year (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    pass_year YEAR
);

INSERT INTO passing_year VALUES
(1,'Manoj',2023),
(2,'Sneha',2024);


/* CURDATE() FUNCTION */
CREATE TABLE attendance (
    attendance_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    attendance_date DATE DEFAULT CURDATE()
);

INSERT INTO attendance (attendance_id, name) VALUES
(1,'Rohit'),
(2,'Divya');


/*  CURTIME() FUNCTION */
CREATE TABLE shift_time (
    emp_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    login_time TIME DEFAULT CURTIME()
);

INSERT INTO shift_time (emp_id, name) VALUES
(1,'Sunil'),
(2,'Pooja');


/*  NOW() FUNCTION */
CREATE TABLE feedback (
    feedback_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(50),
    feedback_time DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
);

INSERT INTO feedback (feedback_id, name) VALUES
(1,'Karthik'),
(2,'Meena');
